hood /hʊd/

(hoods) 

1. N-COUNT A hood is a part of a coat which you can pull up to cover your head. It is in the shape of a triangular bag attached to the neck of the coat at the back. (连在外套上的) 风帽 

例： She threw back the hood of her cloak. 她把披风上的风帽向后甩去。 

2. N-COUNT The hood of a car is the metal cover over the engine at the front. (汽车的) 引擎罩 [美国英语] 

3. N hoodlum的缩写 [slang]  →  short for hoodlum 

4. V to cover or provide with or as if with a hood 覆盖

